# Azure Deployment Plan for INTEXII (Backend)

## Goal

Deploy the backend service in `backend/INTEXII.API` to Azure using AZD + Bicep.

## Project Information

- App Name: INTEXII backend API
- Stack: .NET 10 ASP.NET Core Web API
- Service Path: `backend/INTEXII.API`
- Hosting Target: Azure App Service (Linux)
- Local Data: SQLite files exist locally; for this deployment we will package app and run as-is.

## Azure Resources Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
svc["INTEXII API (.NET)"] --> app["Azure App Service"]
app --> ai["Application Insights"]
app --> log["Log Analytics Workspace"]
```

## Recommended Azure Resources

- Azure App Service Plan: Basic B1 (suitable for dev/test API workloads)
- Azure App Service (Linux): .NET runtime host for backend
- Application Insights: request/trace telemetry
- Log Analytics Workspace: centralized logs for diagnostics

## Supporting Services and Security

- Managed Identity: System-assigned identity on App Service
- App Settings to configure after deploy as needed:
  - `ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT`
  - `FrontendUrl`
  - `Authentication__Google__ClientId`
  - `Authentication__Google__ClientSecret`
  - `Authentication__Jwt__SigningKey`

## Execution Steps

- [ ] Generate AZD files for backend service
- [ ] Create/select AZD environment
- [ ] Set subscription and region
- [ ] Provision Azure resources
- [ ] Deploy backend application
- [ ] Validate health endpoint
- [ ] Summarize deployment output and endpoints

## Status

In Progress
